      "id": "section-0",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "para-0-0",
          "content": "The phrase \"Meet us in the browser\" originated in Figma's 2016 manifesto, championing browser-native tools for real-time collaborative design without downloads or paywalls.Figma co-founder Dylan Field highlighted the browser's power to enable multiplayer editing, cross-platform access, and a shift from siloed to shared workflows, challenging traditional design software like Adobe.This vision propelled Figma from a 2013 seed round to its 2024 IPO as tech's largest design exit.",
