    {
      "id": "section-1",
      "title": "Figma's Browser Bet Sparks Design Industry Shift",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "para-1-0",
          "content": "Figma's 2016 launch bet on browser-native design, enabling simultaneous editing and shared libraries that democratized access for designers, developers, and teams.Field noted initial backlash from those fearing loss of control and over-demystification, yet praised the browser's non-hierarchical nature for fostering \"our ideas\" over \"my ideas.\"By 2023, features like Dev Mode streamlined design-to-code handoffs, solidifying browser workflows for remote collaboration.",
          "citations": [
            {
              "primarySource": {
                "id": "source-7",
                "name": "design",
