                  "title": "Meet us in the browser"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "para-2-1",
          "content": "Dia envisions AI chats as the \"next Chrome,\" predicting they will replace default browsers in five years via tool calls and seamless interactions.Security concerns arise as workflows concentrate in tabs, demanding advanced protections for AI-web hybrids.Optimism persists for Dia's alpha, balancing user frustration with forward momentum in browser evolution.",
